org.apache.ambari.server.api.predicate.expressions

Interface Expression<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractExpression, LogicalExpression, NotLogicalExpression, RelationalExpression

    public interface Expression<T>
    Expression representation. There are two types of expressions, relational and logical. Each expression has an operator and either 2 operands for binary expressions or 1 operand for unary expressions.

    • Method Detail

      • merge

        List<Expression> merge(Expression left,
                       Expression right,
                       int precedence)
        Merge expression with surrounding expressions.
        Parameters:
        left - the preceding expression
        right - the following expression
        precedence - the precedence level being merged. Only expressions at this precedence level should be merged. Others should simply return the left expression, themselves and the right expression in that order.
        Returns:
        a list of expressions after merging. Do not return any null elements.
